  <summary date="2021-07-27T16:07:27Z" status="Passed House">Energy Emergency Leadership Act

This bill requires the Secretary of Energy to assign energy emergency and energy security functions to an Assistant Secretary, including responsibilities with respect to infrastructure and cybersecurity.

The Department of Energy must ensure that such functions are performed in coordination with relevant federal agencies.</summary>
